hin mathematical, logical, scientific, or verbal systems, including algebra problems, analogies, vocabulary, and logical reasoning problems. The book explores basic concepts in group problem solving, social combination models, group memory, group ability and world knowledge tasks, rule induction problems, letters-to-numbers problems, evidence for positive group-to-individual transfer, and social choice theory. The conclusion proposes ten generalizations that are supported by the theory and research on group problem solving. Group Problem Solving is an essential resource for decision-making research in social and cognitive psychology, but also extremely relevant to multidisciplinary and multicultural problem-solving teams in organizational behavior, business administration, management, and behavioral economics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aGroup problem solving. 0aProblem solving. 0aSmall groups. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Social Psychology.2bisacsh  aIGI design.  aIII design.  aU.S. Constitution.  aalgebra.  acollective group response.  acollective induction.  acommon knowledge effect.  aconceptual system.  acooperative group.  acooperative groups.  acooperative problem solving.  ademonstrability.  agroup ability composition.  agroup ability.  agroup choice.  agroup judgment.  agroup members.  agroup memory.  agroup performance.  agroup problem solving.  agroup process.  agroup product.  agroup recognition memory.  agroup response.  agroup structure.  agroup task.  agroup tasks.  agroup-to-individual problem-solving.  ahigh-ability persons.  ahypothesis evaluation.  ahypothesis formation.  aindividual problem solving.  ainduction.  ainformation.  aintellective tasks.  aintellective-judgmental continuum.  ajudgmental tasks.  aletters-to-numbers pro